name: MANDAKHNARAN
bio: [('Additional Information', "GeneralOLYMPIC CONTROVERSYAt the 2016 Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro, he was defeated in his bronze medal contest after judges awarded a decisive penalty point to his opponent, Uzbekistani Ikhtiyor Navruzov, after the fight had ended. Ganzorig had been leading by one point with 18 seconds remaining when he began celebrating while dancing around his opponent's attempts to wrestle, and was then carried around the ring by one of his coaches. He was penalised for not engaging with his opponent, and Navruzov was handed the victory by virtue of having scored the last point of the contest. His coaches, Tserenbaatar Tsogbayar and Byambarinchen Bayaraa, then protested by stripping off their clothes and shoes and throwing them to the floor. The two coaches were given a three-year ban from international wrestling. (bbc.co.uk, 21 Sep 2016; latimes.com, 21 Sep 2016; reuters.com, 21 Aug 2016) "), ('Languages', 'Mongolian'), ('Highlights', 'RankEventYearLocationAsian Games1Freestyle Bantamweight2010Guangzhou, CHNOlympic Games5Freestyle 65 kg2016Rio de Janeiro, BRAWorld Championships3Freestyle 65 kg2014Tashkent, UZB3Freestyle Lightweight2013Budapest, HUN5Freestyle 65 kg2015Las Vegas, NV, USA11Freestyle 70 kg2017Paris, FRA23Freestyle Bantamweight2009Herning, DEN40Freestyle Bantamweight2011Istanbul, TURGolden Grand Prix9Freestyle 65 kg2015Baku, AZEAsian Championships2Freestyle 74 kg2018Bishkek, KGZ2Freestyle Lightweight2013New Delhi, IND2Freestyle Bantamweight2009Pattaya, THA3Freestyle 65 kg2015Doha, QAT')]
